Abuja-based singer and songwriter, Aghayedo Kelvins Eghosa popularly known as Eghe Nimose has released his first music video from the RumbaDub album. The video, “Let you go’ remix featured American rapper and music executive Terry L Johnson (Wordplay T Jay) and Nigerian sensational afrobeat singer and producer Ochelebe Bernard Oko (SOJ Da Legend). In the song, Nimose addresses emotional and psychological abuse, which was well delivered in the video with a fusion of rap and highlife. He said in a statement, “The song was previously released as a single Let you go in the genre of dub /dancehall. This remix was added to the RumbaDub album after the intercontinental collaboration and was released under StarCloud Records and also Miracle World Entertainment, Bordeaux France.” The video is also available on his official YouTube channel.